cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of an ensemble of classifiers and boosting, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with tracking in video sequences, which falls under the subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of an oracle to co-train the ensemble, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
